d 'CVMTEST': module to perform a two-sample Cramer-von Mises equality-of-distributions test
d
d  cvmtest performs a (optionally weighted) two-sample Cramer-von
d Mises (CVM) permutation test to assess whether two samples come
d from the same distribution. The CVM statistic sums the squared
d discrepancy between the two empirical cumulative distribution
d functions (ECDFs) across every distinct value in the combined
d sample, with no variance standardization, making it best suited
d to detecting a discrepancy that is diffuse across the
d distribution, and less sensitive than Kolmogorov-Smirnov (kstest)
d to a single large, localized discrepancy or than Anderson-Darling
d (adtest) to a discrepancy concentrated in the tails. The
d permutation test provides a valid p-value by comparing the
d observed statistic to its distribution under random reassignment
d of group labels. 
d
d KW: equality of distributions
d KW: two-sample
d KW: comparisons
d KW: weighting
d
d Requires: Stata version 11
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260717
d
d Author: Ariel Linden, Linden Consulting Group, LLC
d Support: email alinden@@lindenconsulting.org
d
f cvmtest.ado
f cvmtest.sthlp
